cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is about a deep reinforcement learning architecture for optimal control tasks, which involves the use of neural networks as function approximators. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with control tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel architecture for deep reinforcement learning, which could be of interest to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
